element TargetAudiences
diagram
properties
content complex
children Audience Un-structuredAudiences
used by
element RecordMetadata
source <xs:element name="TargetAudiences">
  <xs:complexType>
    <xs:choice>
      <xs:element name="Audience" maxOccurs="unbounded">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>Repetitive concept where the target audiences are written one by one. (Predetermined list: 01. Expert (High). 02. Knowledgeable (Medium). 03. General (Low).
</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
        <xs:simpleType>
          <xs:restriction base="xs:string">
            <xs:enumeration value="Expert">
              <xs:annotation>
                <xs:documentation>Professionals on Biodiversity (researchers, decision makers, students of higher levels, etc.). By training and experience they have a good knowledge of scientific terminology and taxonomic and nomenclatural issues.</xs:documentation>
              </xs:annotation>
            </xs:enumeration>
            <xs:enumeration value="Knowledgeable">
              <xs:annotation>
                <xs:documentation>Public interest in the knowledge of living organisms but whose training and experience is not directly linked to knowledge of biodiversity, or to be enjoined, their training has not been directly related to biodiversity (professionals from other areas of knowledge, students, amateurs, etc.). Your level of interest is high but not usually use and know the terminology, taxonomy and scientific nomenclature.</xs:documentation>
              </xs:annotation>
            </xs:enumeration>
            <xs:enumeration value="General">
              <xs:annotation>
                <xs:documentation>General Public (anyone interested in living organisms). Persons interested on biodiversity, frequently or timely, but lack the training, expertise or basic knowledge on terminology, taxonomy or scientific nomenclature.</xs:documentation>
              </xs:annotation>
            </xs:enumeration>
          </xs:restriction>
        </xs:simpleType>
      </xs:element>
      <xs:element name="Un-structuredAudiences" type="NormalString">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>List audience codes separated by means of comma or /.</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:element>
    </xs:choice>
  </xs:complexType>
</xs:element>
